cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of segmenting neuronal cells in microscopy images using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new deep learning model called deep complete bipartite networks (CB-Net), which is a modification of fully convolutional networks (FCN). This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with a specific application in neuroscience, which may suggest the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with biomedical imaging, which may suggest the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
